{{Top|legends=Petition of 2000}}
{{Update|[[Star Wars: The Rebel Files]]}}
The '''Petition of 2,000''' was a document signed by the entirety of the [[senator]]s in the [[Delegation of 2,000]], formally protesting [[Supreme Chancellor]] [[Darth Sidious|Sheev Palpatine's]] actions during the [[Clone Wars]], and requesting that he cede the emergency powers he had claimed back to the [[Galactic Senate]] following the conclusion of the war,<ref name="Meena Tills">{{Databank|meena-tills|Meena Tills}}</ref> which the delegation demanded should end with a cease-fire negotiated with the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems]] to stop the bloodshed. By stopping the war, the delegation hoped Palpatine would lack any excuses to continue altering the [[Galactic Constitution]].<ref name="Rebel Files">''[[Star Wars: The Rebel Files]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The Petition of 2,000 was made [[canon]] with a mention of it in [[Meena Tills]]'s old [[Encyclopedia (StarWars.com)|Encyclopedia]] entry on [[StarWars.com]].<ref name="Meena Tills SWE">{{SWE|characters|meenatills|Meena Tills}}</ref> The [[Petition of 2000|Petition of 2,000]] first appeared in [[Matthew Stover]]'s [[Star Wars: Revenge of the Sith (novelization)|novelization]] of the [[2005]] film [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']].<ref name="novelization">[[Star Wars: Revenge of the Sith (novelization)|''Star Wars: Revenge of the Sith'' novelization]]</ref> The scene in which the Petition of 2,000 was proposed was deleted from the film's final cut.<ref name="Revenge of the Sith">{{Film|III}}</ref>

